\begin{theorem}[B3 endpoint transport, paper-local finite form]\label{thm:b3-endpoint-transport}
Inside the certified endpoint-24 quotient by the verified free $T/K$ action, an endpoint orbit is a B3 support-action carrier if and only if its selected value set is non-affine over $\mathbb F_2^4$.  Equivalently, the exact B3 endpoint selector is \texttt{selected\_value\_nonaffine}.  It selects 15 quotient orbits and 60 records, and these 15 orbits are precisely the Item7-H lower-geometry transport atoms with support-action labels \texttt{STEP6-SA01},\ldots,\texttt{STEP6-SA15}.
\end{theorem}
